<br>
The answer is Thursday..since the &quot;today&quot; is Wednesday.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> When the day after tomorrow is yesterday, today will be as far from Wednesday <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just assumed that &quot;today&quot; was Wednesday..so...day after tomorrow would Friday, and the day that makes Friday yesterday would be..Saturday.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> far from Wednesday as today was from Wednesday when the day before yesterday was tomorrow<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Still assuming &quot;today&quot; is Wednesday..so...the day before yesterday is Monday..and to make Monday tomorrow, you're talking about Sunday.  <br>
<br>
Saturday from the first statement, is the same distance from Wednesday as Sunday is.<br>
<br>
*crosses his fingers in hopes that he's not utterly embarrassed by being wrong* <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19091
