<br>
The idea is to take number and letter clues to form a commonly known phrase.  For instance:<br>
<br>
7 W of the A W = 7 Wonders of the Ancient World<br>
32 D F at which W F = 32 Degrees Fahrenheit at which Water Freezes<br>
<br>
And so, to try and keep this nifty thread going, here's an easy one:<br>
<br>
366 D in a L Y <p>Malinki Nuikila<BR>
